title: Mock-treated BMSC sample M48
source_name_ch1: Reference sample: pool of 5 samples of bone marrow-derived mesenchymal stromal cells
characteristics_ch1: tissue: Bone marrow-derived mesenchymal stromal cells
treatment_protocol_ch1: Five million detached BM-hMSCs were concentrated at 30 x 106 cells/ml in HBSS, without Ca2+ or Mg2+ (Gibco), containing 10 mM HEPES, 0.1 % human serum albumin (Sigma-Aldrich). Each sample was divided into two reaction tubes, buffer alone, and the other with 60 mU/ml of FTVI or FTVII (obtained from R&D Systems), as specified in each case, containing  1 mM GDP-fucose (Sigma-Aldrich) as enzyme substrate. Reactions were performed at 37 oC for 1 h with gentle shaking, followed by centrifugation and washing with DPBS.
growth_protocol_ch1: BM mononuclear cells (BMMNC) were isolated by density gradient centrifugation over Histopaque-1077 (Sigma-Aldrich, St Louis, MO).  Human Platelet Lysate was obtained from platelet concentrates, which were frozen at –80 ºC for at least 3 days, thawed at 37 oC, transferred to sterile tubes and centrifuged at 900 g for 30 min; the supernatants were pooled, aliquoted and stored at –20ºC. BMMNC were seeded in culture flasks at 160,000 cells/cm2 using low glucose DMEM (GIBCO Invitrogen Corporation, Gran Island, NY, USA) supplemented with 5 % HPL, plus 50 U/ml penicillin and 50 U/ml streptomycin, and heparin (2U/ml) incubated at 37oC in a humid atmosphere with 5 % CO2. First change of medium was performed at 24 h and from this point twice per week. First passage was made when cells achieved 60-80% confluence. Culture media was removed and culture flasks were washed with DPBS, then incubated with TrypLE Select reagent (GIBCO Invitrogen Corporation, Gran Island, NY, USA). Cells were pooled, centrifuged at 700 g for 5 min and seeded at a density of 1,000 cells/cm2. After the third passage, BM-hMSCs were harvested.
extract_protocol_ch1: RNAs were isolated using the miRNeasy mini kit (Qiagen) protocol following the manufacturer's instructions
label_protocol_ch1: Agilent Two Color Quick Amp Labeling and RNA Spike-In kits protocols following the manufacturer's instructions

title: FTVI-treated BMSC sample RP-003-P2
source_name_ch1: Reference sample: pool of 5 samples of bone marrow-derived mesenchymal stromal cells
characteristics_ch1: tissue: Bone marrow-derived mesenchymal stromal cells
treatment_protocol_ch1: Five million detached BM-hMSCs were concentrated at 30 x 106 cells/ml in HBSS, without Ca2+ or Mg2+ (Gibco), containing 10 mM HEPES, 0.1 % human serum albumin (Sigma-Aldrich). Each sample was divided into two reaction tubes, buffer alone, and the other with 60 mU/ml of FTVI or FTVII (obtained from R&D Systems), as specified in each case, containing  1 mM GDP-fucose (Sigma-Aldrich) as enzyme substrate. Reactions were performed at 37 oC for 1 h with gentle shaking, followed by centrifugation and washing with DPBS.
growth_protocol_ch1: BM mononuclear cells (BMMNC) were isolated by density gradient centrifugation over Histopaque-1077 (Sigma-Aldrich, St Louis, MO).  Human Platelet Lysate was obtained from platelet concentrates, which were frozen at –80 ºC for at least 3 days, thawed at 37 oC, transferred to sterile tubes and centrifuged at 900 g for 30 min; the supernatants were pooled, aliquoted and stored at –20ºC. BMMNC were seeded in culture flasks at 160,000 cells/cm2 using low glucose DMEM (GIBCO Invitrogen Corporation, Gran Island, NY, USA) supplemented with 5 % HPL, plus 50 U/ml penicillin and 50 U/ml streptomycin, and heparin (2U/ml) incubated at 37oC in a humid atmosphere with 5 % CO2. First change of medium was performed at 24 h and from this point twice per week. First passage was made when cells achieved 60-80% confluence. Culture media was removed and culture flasks were washed with DPBS, then incubated with TrypLE Select reagent (GIBCO Invitrogen Corporation, Gran Island, NY, USA). Cells were pooled, centrifuged at 700 g for 5 min and seeded at a density of 1,000 cells/cm2. After the third passage, BM-hMSCs were harvested.
extract_protocol_ch1: RNAs were isolated using the miRNeasy mini kit (Qiagen) protocol following the manufacturer's instructions
label_protocol_ch1: Agilent Two Color Quick Amp Labeling and RNA Spike-In kits protocols following the manufacturer's instructions

treatment_protocol_ch2: Five million detached BM-hMSCs were concentrated at 30 x 106 cells/ml in HBSS, without Ca2+ or Mg2+ (Gibco), containing 10 mM HEPES, 0.1 % human serum albumin (Sigma-Aldrich). Each sample was divided into two reaction tubes, buffer alone, and the other with 60 mU/ml of FTVI or FTVII (obtained from R&D Systems), as specified in each case, containing  1 mM GDP-fucose (Sigma-Aldrich) as enzyme substrate. Reactions were performed at 37 oC for 1 h with gentle shaking, followed by centrifugation and washing with DPBS.
growth_protocol_ch2: BM mononuclear cells (BMMNC) were isolated by density gradient centrifugation over Histopaque-1077 (Sigma-Aldrich, St Louis, MO).  Human Platelet Lysate was obtained from platelet concentrates, which were frozen at –80 ºC for at least 3 days, thawed at 37 oC, transferred to sterile tubes and centrifuged at 900 g for 30 min; the supernatants were pooled, aliquoted and stored at –20ºC. BMMNC were seeded in culture flasks at 160,000 cells/cm2 using low glucose DMEM (GIBCO Invitrogen Corporation, Gran Island, NY, USA) supplemented with 5 % HPL, plus 50 U/ml penicillin and 50 U/ml streptomycin, and heparin (2U/ml) incubated at 37oC in a humid atmosphere with 5 % CO2. First change of medium was performed at 24 h and from this point twice per week. First passage was made when cells achieved 60-80% confluence. Culture media was removed and culture flasks were washed with DPBS, then incubated with TrypLE Select reagent (GIBCO Invitrogen Corporation, Gran Island, NY, USA). Cells were pooled, centrifuged at 700 g for 5 min and seeded at a density of 1,000 cells/cm2. After the third passage, BM-hMSCs were harvested.
extract_protocol_ch2: RNAs were isolated using the miRNeasy mini kit (Qiagen) protocol following the manufacturer's instructions
label_protocol_ch2: Agilent Two Color Quick Amp Labeling and RNA Spike-In kits protocols following the manufacturer's instructions
hyb_protocol: Agilent Gene Expression Hybridization kit protocol following the manufacturer's instructions
scan_protocol: Agilent G2565CA scanner, Agilent Scan Control software, scanning at 3µm
contact_institute: Hospital Clinico Universitario Virgen de la Arrixaca
